          "id": "msg_001_1",
          "role": "user",
          "content": "I need a lesson plan for introducing fractions to my 5th graders. Many of them are ELL students.",
          "timestamp": "2025-02-20T14:30:00Z"
        },
        {
          "id": "msg_001_2",
          "role": "assistant",
          "content": "I'll create a fractions lesson plan designed for your 5th grade class with ELL students. Let me align it to Common Core standards.\n\n## Lesson: Understanding Fractions as Numbers\n\n**Standards:** 5.NF.A.1 - Add and subtract fractions with unlike denominators\n\n**Learning Objectives:**\n- Students will understand fractions as numbers on the number line\n- Students will visualize fractions using area models\n- Students will compare fractions with unlike denominators\n\n**Essential Question:** How can we represent parts of a whole and compare them?\n\n**Differentiation for ELL:**\n- Visual supports with fraction tiles and manipulatives\n- Vocabulary bank with pictures (numerator, denominator, equivalent)\n- Sentence frames for mathematical discourse\n- Partner work with mixed-language pairing\n\nWould you like me to expand any section or add specific activities?",
          "timestamp": "2025-02-20T14:30:45Z"
        },
        {
          "id": "msg_001_3",
          "role": "user",
          "content": "/generate --unitFocus \"Introduction to Fractions\" --lessonLength 60 --essentialQuestions \"How do fractions represent parts of a whole?\"",
